    pearls: ["Excisional biopsy is mandatory for lymphoma diagnosis - FNA cannot assess nodal architecture needed to distinguish HL from NHL subtypes","Reed-Sternberg cells are pathognomonic for Hodgkin lymphoma: CD15+/CD30+ large binucleated cells with owl-eye appearance","The Ann Arbor stage alone does not determine treatment; the International Prognostic Score (IPS) for HL and IPI for NHL incorporate age, LDH, ECOG status, and extranodal sites","Alcohol-induced lymph node pain is rare but nearly pathognomonic for Hodgkin lymphoma","Double-hit lymphoma (concurrent MYC and BCL2 rearrangements) is highly aggressive and requires intensified chemotherapy (DA-EPOCH-R), not standard R-CHOP","Tumor lysis syndrome risk is highest with Burkitt lymphoma and other highly proliferative tumors; rasburicase is contraindicated in G6PD deficiency"],
