        correct: 1,
        rationale: "Morphine and codeine cause direct, non-IgE-mediated mast cell degranulation by binding to MrgprX2 receptors on mast cells. This can trigger severe mediator release in MCAS patients. Fentanyl and hydromorphone are safer opioid alternatives as they cause minimal direct mast cell activation."
